    <p class="subhead raleway">Craft beautiful websites for an <span class="desktop"><br></span>exquisite user&nbsp;experience</p>
  </div>
</div> #}
{% endblock %}

{% block content %}
<img src="img/wave-divider-dark.svg" class="wave-divider top">
<section class="web-dev-bio" id="web-dev-bio">
  <div class="copy-container">
    <h2 class="headline righteous copy">Jack of all trades, <span class="nowrap">Master of some</span></h2>
    <p class="body copy">My philosophy towards my work emphasizes a
      <em>Jack of all trades, Master of <span><strong>some</strong></span></em> approach. As a Front End Developer, my
      purview includes working with designers to bring mockups to life, effectively integrating with backend
      arhitecture, understanding the product strategy, and of course, creating interfaces for the best user
      experience possible.<br><br>
      While building websites and applications on the client side is my primary focus, I also maintain
      proficiency with Back End fundamentals, Creative Design tools, and Project Management skills.
    </p>
  </div>
  <div class="all-icons">
    <div class="icon-container d-flex">
      {% for icon in icons %}
        <div class="logo" id="{{ icon }}-logo">
          <img src="img/{{ icon }}.png" alt="{{ icon }} logo">
          <p class="caption">{{ icon|capitalize }}</p>
          </div>
      {% endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="icon-rows">
    <div class="icon-container d-flex row row-1">
      {% for icon in row_1 %}
        <div class="logo" id="{{ icon }}-logo">
          <img src="img/{{ icon }}.png" alt="{{ icon }} logo">
          <p class="caption">{{ icon|capitalize }}</p>
          </div>
      {% endfor %}
    </div>
    <div class="icon-container d-flex row row-2">
      {% for icon in row_2 %}
        <div class="logo" id="{{ icon }}-logo">
          <img src="img/{{ icon }}.png" alt="{{ icon }} logo">
          <p class="caption">{{ icon|capitalize }}</p>
          </div>
      {% endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

{# Dev Process - Plan, Design, Develop #}
<div class="bg-black d-flex container-fluid" id="dev-process">
  {# Card 1 #}
  <div class="d-flex align-items-center process-card">
    <div>
      <h3>Plan <i class="far fa-lightbulb desktop"></i>
      </h3>
      <p>Clear vision, solid goals</p>
    </div>
    <div class="process-icon mobile">
      <i class="far fa-lightbulb"></i>
    </div>
  </div>
  {# Card 2 #}
  <div class="d-flex align-items-center process-card">
    <div>
      <h3>Design <i class="fas fa-palette desktop"></i>
      </h3>
      <p>Look, feel, experience</p>
    </div>
    <div class="process-icon mobile">
      <i class="fas fa-palette"></i>
    </div>
  </div>
  {# Card 3 #}
  <div class="d-flex align-items-center process-card">
    <div>
      <h3>Develop <i class="fas fa-laptop-code desktop"></i></h3>
      <p>Elegant, responsive, secure</p>
    </div>
    <div class="process-icon mobile">
      <i class="fas fa-laptop-code"></i>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<div id="portfolio">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="row">
      <div class="col-lg-12 mx-auto">
        <div id="dev-title">
          <h2 class="copy righteous heading">Web Dev</h2>
          <p>As a Web Developer I've had the chance to work with diverse clients, from small volunteer community groups to international industry leaders. <br><br>
            When taking on a project, I provide my clients with more than just a robotic output of code in a folder. I give them a <strong><em>partner</em></strong> – a holistic, human approach that considers budget, scope, timeline, audience, and existing assets to deliver the best possible&nbsp;solution, tailored to a client's unique&nbsp;needs.</p>      
        </div>
        <div class="card-container flex-wrap">

          {# Google #}
          <div class="card no-shadow" id="google-card">
            <div id="carousel-google-controls" class="carousel slide" data-ride="carousel" data-interval="3000">
              <div class="carousel-inner">
                <div class="carousel-item active">
                  <img class="d-block w-100" src="img/google-home-hub.jpg" alt="First slide">
                </div>
                <div class="carousel-item">
                  <img class="d-block w-100" src="img/home-mini.jpg" alt="Second slide">
                </div>
                <div class="carousel-item">
                  <img class="d-block w-100" src="img/chromecast.jpg" alt="Third slide">
                </div>
                <div class="carousel-item">
                  <img class="d-block w-100" src="img/google-nest.jpg" alt="Fourth slide">
                </div>
              </div>
              <a class="carousel-control-prev" href="#carousel-google-controls" role="button" data-slide="prev">
                <span class="carousel-control-prev-icon" aria-hidden="true"></span>
                <span class="sr-only">Previous</span>
              </a>
              <a class="carousel-control-next" href="#carousel-google-controls" role="button" data-slide="next">
                <span class="carousel-control-next-icon" aria-hidden="true"></span>
                <span class="sr-only">Next</span>
              </a>
            </div>
            <div class="card-body">
              <img src="img/google-logo.png" alt="Google" class="google-logo d-block card-title">
              <p class="card-text">I build responsive marketing emails and websites for Google clients. Along with HTML and LESS/CSS, my
                build process utilizes Nunjucks templating, personalized data integration,
                localization, and accessibility best practices.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          {# Healthworker housing #}
          <div class="card no-shadow" id="healthworker-card">
            <div class="overlay-container">
              <img src="img/health-worker-housing-mockup.png" class="img-fluid img-card-top" alt="Mock up of website">
              <div class="overlay">
                <div class="text">
                  <p>A volunteer-run Covid-19 relief project</p>
                  <a href="projects/covid_ny/deploy/index.html">
                    <button type="button" class="btn btn-primary">Visit site</button>
                  </a>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="card-body">
              <h5 class="card-title">Health Worker Housing</h5>
              <p class="card-text">At the start of the Covid-19 outbreak, I joined a volunteer initiative to connect
                healthcare workers with secondary housing to insulate their families from added risk. The site was
                designed to be simple, easily scalable, and
                deployed as fast as possible.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>

          {# Mono Lake #}
          <div class="card">
            <img src="img/mono-lake.jpg" alt="" class="card-img-top">
            <div class="card-body">
              <h5 class="card-title">
                Mono Basin Watch
              </h5>
              <p class="card-text">
                MBW is a community group preserving the natural beauty of Mono Basin, CA. I helped MBW leverage a modest budget to develop a crowd-sourced system of tracking environmentally dangerous activities, supporting county preservation efforts.<br>
                <a href="https://monobasinwatch.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="dark-link">Check it out &raquo;</a>
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>

          {# To-do list #}
          {# <div class="card no-shadow" id="to-do-card">
            <div class="card-header">
              <h5 class="card-title">To-Do List</h5>
              <p class="card-text">A basic to-do list app to organize tasks for the day. You can add new tasks, remove
